HEADWORD: Exilition
<hw>Ex`i*li"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exsilire</ets> to spring from; <ets>ex</ets> out +
<ets>salire</ets> to spring, leap.]</ety> <def>A sudden springing or
leaping out.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

